<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Become a voters</h2>
        <ul>
            <p>To register to vote and vote in a North Carolina county, a person have to meet the qualification.</p>
            <li><i>be a U.S. citizen</i></li>
            <li><i>be at least 18 years of age, or be 17 years of age and will turn 18 no later than November 8, 2016 (the date of the general election)</i></li>
            <li><i>reside in the county and election district in which he or she presents to vote</i></li>
            <li><i>not be serving an active sentence for a felony conviction</i></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Get Voting station location</h2>
        <ul>
            <p>Getting trouble on finding voting station. NC vote provides GPS map function to help you get the voting station location.</p>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Information of Candidate</h2>
        <ul>
            <p>Looking for more information about the candidates?</p>
            <p>NCmyVote provides most updating information about election.</p>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Forms</h2>
        <ul>
            <p>Click here to down the voter application form.</p>
            <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="http://www.ncsbe.gov/Portals/0/FilesP/NCVRRegFormv102013eng.pdf" target="_blank">Download Form &raquo;</a></p>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
